    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<p><b>N</b> equidistant nodes numbered 1,2,3......N lie in an (N-1) dimensional space. A data packet keeps jumping between these nodes indefinitely. Every second, the data packet can move from its current node to any of the free <b> N - 1 </b> nodes with equal probability. </p>\n<p>\nGiven its initial position <b>'a'</b>, answer <b>'Q'</b> queries of the form:\n<b>t i</b> : Find the number of distinct paths which result in the packet being on node i after t seconds. \n</p>\n<p>\nAs the answer can be very large, print it modulo 1000000007. \n</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<hr>\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line contains two space separated integers <b>N</b> and <b>Q</b> , the number of nodes in the space and the number of queries respectively.</p>\n<p>The next line of input contains a single integer <b>a</b>, the initial node of the packet.</p>\n<p><b>Q</b> lines follow. In each line, there are two space separated integers <b>t</b> and <b>i</b> as described in the problem statement.\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<hr>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Print the answer modulo 1000000007 for each query in a new line.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<hr>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N, Q, t</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>5</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>a, i</b> \u2264 <b>N</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<hr>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n3 4\n1\n1 1\n2 3 \n4 1 \n3 2\n<b>Output:</b>\n0\n1\n6\n3\n\n</pre>\n",
